-- Cersanit, Dr Kendy, PGF, Zachodni May Move: Central European Stock Preview
-- Marta Waldoch
-- 2010-09-13T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-12/cersanit-dr-kendy-mol-zachodni-may-move-central-europe-stock-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in central
European markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names. Share prices are from the last close.  
 Poland’s  WIG20 Index  fell 0.5 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
dropped 0.4 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  lost 1.1 percent.  
 Cersanit SA  (CST PW): Poland’s biggest ceramic tile
producer starts subscription for its rights offer. Cersanit
shares declined 3.6 percent to 10.61 zloty.  
 Dr Kendy SA  (DRK PW): The Polish candy distributor will
start trading on the Warsaw Stock Exchange’s NewConnect market.  
 Mol Nyrt.  (MOL HB): Hungary’s largest oil refiner signed a
450 million-euro ($571 million) credit facility agreement. Mol
Nyrt. shares lost 0.2 percent to 22,150 forint.  
 PGF SA  (PGF PW): Poland’s biggest drug wholesaler was
raised to “hold” from “sell” at Erste Group Bank AG, which
increased its price estimate for the stock 67 percent to 45
zloty. PGF shares gained 0.5 percent to 46.2 zloty.  
 TU Europa SA  (ERP PW): The Polish insurer controlled by
Polish billionaire Leszek Czarnecki resumed plans to sell shares
in a public offering this month. It set a maximum issue price at
160 zloty per share. Europa shares climbed 3.2 percent to 129
zloty when they last traded Sept. 9.  
 Bank Zachodni WBK SA  (BZW PW): Banco Santander SA, Spain’s
biggest bank, agreed to buy Allied Irish Banks Plc’s 70 percent
stake in Zachodni for 2.94 billion euros. Zachodni shares fell 1
percent to 195 zloty.  PKO Bank Polski SA , whose bid to buy AIB’s
unit failed, slipped 0.2 percent to 40.51 zloty.  
